          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The inelastic scattering of 14 MeV neutrons by sodium,",
                "iron, nickel, and lead nuclei"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Flight base is 6. m.",
                "        Time resolution (half-width) 3.E-8 sec.",
                " Inelastically scattered neutrons spectra were measured",
                "in the energy range 0.6 - 4.0 MeV. Spectra were not",
                "corrected for contribution from (N,2N) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STANK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Liquid scintillator of 150 cm3 volume with",
                "FEU-33 photomultiplier."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Of compiler. It is not explained in the article, how",
                " cross-sections were derived from measured spectra -",
                " full energy range was used or only energy rage of",
                " measurement 0.6 - 4.0 MeV. These cross sections are",
                " explained by authors as \"cross section of non-elastic",
                " neutron scattering leading to residual nucleus in",
                " higher (10-14 MeV) excited states\"."
              ]
            }
          ],
